preferences.cli.daemonDebug: Enable debug logging of the gRPC calls to the Arduino CLI. A restart of the IDE is needed for this setting to take effect. It's false by default.
preferences.cloud.enabled: True if the sketch sync functions are enabled. Defaults to true.
preferences.cloud.pull.warn: True if users should be warned before pulling a cloud sketch. Defaults to true.
preferences.cloud.push.warn: True if users should be warned before pushing a cloud sketch. Defaults to true.
preferences.cloud.pushpublic.warn: True if users should be warned before pushing a public sketch to the cloud. Defaults to true.
preferences.cloud.sketchSyncEndpoint: The endpoint used to push and pull sketches from a backend. By default it points to Arduino Cloud API.
preferences.compile: စက်ဘာသာပြန်
preferences.compile.experimental: True if the IDE should handle multiple compiler errors. False by default
preferences.compile.revealRange: Adjusts how compiler errors are revealed in the editor after a failed verify/upload. Possible values: 'auto': Scroll vertically as necessary and reveal a line. 'center': Scroll vertically as necessary and reveal a line centered vertically. 'top': Scroll vertically as necessary and reveal a line close to the top of the viewport, optimized for viewing a code definition. 'centerIfOutsideViewport': Scroll vertically as necessary and reveal a line centered vertically only if it lies outside the viewport. The default value is '{0}'.
preferences.compile.verbose: True for verbose compile output. False by default
preferences.compile.warnings: Tells gcc which warning level to use. It's 'None' by default
preferences.compilerWarnings: စက်ဘာသာပြန်ကိရိယာသတိပေးချက်များ
preferences.editorFontSize: အယ်ဒီတာဖောင့်အရွယ်အစား
preferences.enterAdditionalURLs: Enter additional URLs, one for each row
preferences.ide.updateBaseUrl: The base URL where to download updates from. Defaults to 'https://downloads.arduino.cc/arduino-ide'
preferences.ide.updateChannel: Release channel to get updated from. 'stable' is the stable release, 'nightly' is the latest development build.
preferences.interfaceScale: အင်တာဖေ့စ်စကေး
preferences.invalid.editorFontSize: Invalid editor font size. It must be a positive integer.
preferences.language.log: True if the Arduino Language Server should generate log files into the sketch folder. Otherwise, false. It's false by default.
preferences.language.realTimeDiagnostics: If true, the language server provides real-time diagnostics when typing in the editor. It's false by default.
preferences.noProxy: ကြားခံကွန်ရက်မရှိ
preferences.showVerbose: နောက်ပါလုပ်နေစဉ် အချက်အလက်များပိုမိုများပြားစွာပြမည်
preferences.sketchbook.showAllFiles: True to show all sketch files inside the sketch. It is false by default.
preferences.survey.notification: True if users should be notified if a survey is available. True by default.
preferences.unofficialBoardSupport: Click for a list of unofficial board support URLs
preferences.upload: အပ်လုတ်တင်
preferences.upload.verbose: True for verbose upload output. False by default.
preferences.verifyAfterUpload: အပ်လုတ်တင်ပြီးလျှင်ကုတ်ကိုစစ်ဆေးပါ
preferences.window.autoScale: True if the user interface automatically scales with the font size.
preferences.window.zoomLevel: Adjust the zoom level of the window. The original size is 0 and each increment above (e.g. 1) or below (e.g. -1) represents zooming 20% larger or smaller. You can also enter decimals to adjust the zoom level with a finer granularity.
